name: Barbell Decline Close Grip To Skull Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a decline bench with your head lower than your feet and hold a barbell with a close grip. | Step:2 Lower the barbell towards your forehead by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary. | Step:3 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms to press the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push-Up Inside Leg Kick
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your feet together. | Step:2 Lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 As you push back up, lift one leg off the ground and kick it out to the side, keeping it straight. | Step:4 Lower your leg back down and repeat the push-up, then switch to the other leg. | Step:5 Continue alternating leg kicks with each push-up repetition.

name: Barbell Press Sit-Up
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back on a mat with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip, resting it on your chest. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your torso is at a 45-degree angle. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Goblet Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell close to your chest with both hands. | Step:2 Keeping your chest up and core engaged, lower your body down into a squat position by bending at the knees and hips. | Step:3 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Chest Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your back flat against the pad. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and position your elbows at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Push the handles forward until your arms are fully extended, exhaling during the movement. | Step:4 Pause briefly at the end of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position, inhaling as you do so. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward, and arms fully extended. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: One Arm Against Wall
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a wall with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend one arm straight out in front of you and place your palm against the wall. | Step:3 Engage your core and lean your body forward, keeping your arm straight and your back flat. | Step:4 Slowly push against the wall with your palm, activating your lat muscles. | Step:5 Hold the position for a few seconds, then release and repeat with the other arm.

name: Close-Grip Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands placed close together, directly under your shoulders. | Step:2 Engage your core and lower your body towards the ground, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:3 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in one hand at shoulder level, palm facing forward. | Step:2 Press the dumbbell upward until your arm is fully extended overhead. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Cable Standing Up Straight Crossovers
instructions: Step:1 Stand in the middle of a cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hold the handles of the cables with your palms facing down and your arms extended straight out to the sides. | Step:3 Keeping your arms straight, bring your hands together in front of your body, crossing them over each other. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly return to the starting position, keeping your arms extended. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Side Bend
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in one hand, letting it hang down by your side. | Step:2 Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, slowly bend sideways at the waist towards the opposite side of the dumbbell, lowering the weight as far as you comfortably can. | Step:3 Pause for a moment, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides and repeat.

name: Sledge Hammer
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the sledge hammer with both hands. | Step:2 Engage your core and keep your back straight. | Step:3 Swing the sledge hammer down towards the ground, using your core and upper body strength. | Step:4 As you swing down, pivot your hips and transfer the force to the hammer. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Assisted Wide-Grip Chest Dip (Kneeling)
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the machine to your desired height and secure your knees on the pad. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with a wide grip and keep your elbows slightly bent. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the floor. | Step:4 Push yourself back up to the starting position by extending your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest Dip On Straight Bar
instructions: Step:1 Grab the parallel bars with your palms facing down and your arms fully extended. | Step:2 Bend your knees and cross your ankles. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your arms until your shoulders are below your elbows. | Step:4 Push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Front Raise And Pullover
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:2 Keep your arms straight and raise the barbell in front of you until it reaches shoulder height. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Next, lower the barbell behind your head, keeping your arms straight. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then raise the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Biceps Curl To Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing forward and arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your elbows close to your sides, curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders. | Step:4 Once your forearms are vertical, rotate your wrists so that your palms are facing forward. | Step:5 Press the dumbbells overhead until your arms are fully extended. | Step:6 Lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position by reversing the movement. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Arms Apart Circular Toe Touch (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and arms extended to the sides. | Step:2 Keeping your legs straight, bend forward at the waist and reach down towards your toes with your right hand. | Step:3 As you reach down, simultaneously lift your left leg straight up behind you, maintaining balance. | Step:4 Return to the starting position and repeat the movement with your left hand reaching towards your toes and your right leg lifting up behind you. | Step:5 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Assisted Prone Lying Quads Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on the ground with your legs extended. | Step:2 Bend your left knee and reach back with your left hand to grab your left foot or ankle. | Step:3 Gently pull your left foot towards your glutes, feeling a stretch in your left quad. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, then release. | Step:5 Repeat with your right leg.

name: Lever Preacher Curl V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your upper arms resting on the pad and your chest against the support. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an underhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keep your upper arms stationary and exhale as you curl the handles towards your shoulders, contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale as you slowly lower the handles back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated One Leg Calf Raise - Palm Up
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your back straight and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand and place it on top of your thigh, palm facing up. | Step:3 Lift one leg off the ground and extend it in front of you, keeping your knee slightly bent. | Step:4 Raise your heel as high as possible by pushing through the ball of your foot. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heel back down. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Lying External Shoulder Rotation
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your side on a flat bench with your upper arm against your side and your elbow bent 90 degrees. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in your hand with your palm facing down. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm against your side, slowly rotate your forearm upward as far as possible. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your forearm back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Ez Barbell Seated Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the ez barbell with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Raise the barbell overhead, fully extending your arms. | Step:4 Keeping your upper arms stationary, lower the barbell behind your head by bending your elbows. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then raise the barbell back to the starting position by extending your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Straight Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, hinge at the hips and lower the dumbbells towards the ground, allowing your torso to lean forward. | Step:3 Continue lowering the dumbbells until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings, keeping your knees slightly bent. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then engage your glutes and hamstrings to lift your torso back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Close-Grip Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with a close grip, slightly narrower than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lower the barbell towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Front Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and grasp the cable handle with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Raise the cable handle in front of you, keeping your arms straight and your palms facing down. | Step:4 Continue lifting until your arms are parallel to the floor. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the cable handle back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Lying Triceps Extension V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope handle to a low pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Lie down on a flat bench facing up, with your head towards the cable machine. | Step:3 Grasp the rope handle with both hands, palms facing each other, and extend your arms straight up over your chest. | Step:4 Keeping your upper arms stationary, slowly lower the rope handle towards your forehead by bending your elbows. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then extend your arms back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Alternating Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in each hand at shoulder height. | Step:2 Press one kettlebell overhead, fully extending your arm. | Step:3 Lower the kettlebell back to shoulder height. | Step:4 Repeat with the other arm. | Step:5 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Rope Lying On Floor Tricep Extension
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope to a cable machine and set it to the lowest position. | Step:2 Lie on the floor facing up, with your head towards the cable machine. | Step:3 Hold the rope with both hands, palms facing each other, and extend your arms straight up towards the ceiling. | Step:4 Keep your upper arms stationary and slowly lower the rope towards your forehead, bending your elbows. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bottoms-Up
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Bend your knees and bring them towards your chest, keeping your feet off the ground. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, lift your hips off the ground, bringing your knees towards your head. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Alternate Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with your right hand and bring your arm up so that your upper arm is parallel to the ground and your elbow is bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Keep your upper arm stationary and extend your forearm backward, fully straightening your arm. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with your left arm. | Step:6 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Decline Chest Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a decline bench with a dumbbell in one hand, resting on your chest. | Step:2 Place your feet flat on the ground and keep your back pressed against the bench. | Step:3 Extend your arm and push the dumbbell up towards the ceiling, fully extending your elbow. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Cable Rope High Pulley Overhead Tricep Extension
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope to a high pulley and adjust the weight accordingly. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the pulley machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the rope with both hands, palms facing down, and bring your hands above your head. | Step:4 Keep your upper arms close to your head and perpendicular to the floor. | Step:5 Slowly lower the rope behind your head by bending your elbows. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Supine Reverse Fly
instructions: Step:1 Attach a D-handle to a low pulley cable machine and lie face down on a flat bench. | Step:2 Grasp the D-handle with each hand, palms facing down, and extend your arms straight out in front of you. | Step:3 Keeping your arms straight, raise them out to the sides until they are parallel to the floor. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Revers Grip Concentration Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing up. | Step:2 Rest your elbow on the inside of your thigh, just above the knee. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Barbell Standing Close Grip Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with an underhand grip, hands close together. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and your upper arms stationary throughout the movement. | Step:3 Exhale as you curl the weights while contracting your biceps. Continue to raise the bar until your biceps are fully contracted and the bar is at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale as you slowly begin to bring the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Incline Shoulder Raises
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the smith machine to an incline position. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and core engaged. | Step:5 Raise the barbell up towards the ceiling, leading with your elbows. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sphinx
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on the ground with your forearms flat on the floor, elbows directly under your shoulders. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your chest off the ground, keeping your forearms and toes on the floor. | Step:3 Hold this position for a few seconds, making sure to keep your neck in a neutral position. | Step:4 Slowly lower your chest back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight Kneeling Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Kneel down on the ground with your knees hip-width apart. | Step:2 Place your hands on the ground in front of you, shoulder-width apart, fingers pointing forward. | Step:3 Extend your legs straight behind you, balancing on your toes and hands, forming a straight line from head to heels. | Step:4 Bend your elbows and lower your upper body towards the ground, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your hands to straighten your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Upright Shoulder External Rotation
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body. | Step:2 Raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the ground, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:3 Rotate your arms externally, bringing the dumbbells up towards your head while keeping your elbows in the same position. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Lying Leg Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the machine to fit your body and select the desired weight. | Step:2 Lie face down on the machine with your legs straight and your heels against the padded lever. | Step:3 Grasp the handles or the sides of the machine for stability. | Step:4 Keeping your upper body stationary, exhale and curl your legs up as far as possible without lifting your hips off the pad. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your hamstrings. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the lever back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Reverse Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the band with an overhand grip, palms facing down, and wrap it around your fingers. | Step:3 Rest your forearms on your thighs, with your wrists hanging off the edge. | Step:4 Slowly curl your wrists upward, squeezing your forearms. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your wrists back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight Incline Side Plank
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying on your side with your legs extended and stacked on top of each other. | Step:2 Place your forearm on the ground directly below your shoulder, with your elbow bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Engage your core and lift your hips off the ground, creating a straight line from your head to your feet. | Step:4 Hold this position for the desired amount of time. | Step:5 Lower your hips back down to the ground and repeat on the other side.

name: Barbell Wrist Curl V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent. | Step:2 Hold a barbell with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Rest your forearms on your thighs, allowing your wrists to hang off the edge. | Step:4 Slowly curl your wrists upward, bringing the barbell towards your forearms. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Assisted Prone Rectus Femoris Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on the ground with your legs straight. | Step:2 Bend your right knee and reach back with your right hand to grab your right foot or ankle. | Step:3 Gently pull your right foot or ankle towards your glutes, feeling a stretch in the front of your right thigh. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds. | Step:5 Release and repeat on the other side.

name: Dumbbell Single Arm Overhead Carry
instructions: Step:1 Stand tall with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand. | Step:2 Raise the dumbbell overhead, fully extending your arm. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your back straight as you walk forward, maintaining the dumbbell overhead. | Step:4 Continue walking for the desired distance or time. | Step:5 Switch hands and repeat the exercise.

name: Assisted Chest Dip (Kneeling)
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the machine to your desired height and secure your knees on the pad. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with your palms facing down and your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the floor. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Elevator
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Place your hands on your hips or cross them in front of your chest. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight, slowly bend forward at the waist, lowering your upper body towards the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly raise your upper body back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Kickbacks On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing inwards and your arms bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight back, squeezing your triceps at the top of the movement. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Zottman Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and rotate your palms to face forward. | Step:3 Curl the dumbbells up to your shoulders while keeping your upper arms stationary. | Step:4 At the top of the movement, rotate your wrists so that your palms are facing away from your body. | Step:5 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position, rotating your palms back to facing your body. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Machine Inner Chest Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your back flat against the pad. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and position your elbows at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Push the handles forward until your arms are fully extended, exhaling during the movement. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position, inhaling as you do so. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Assisted Lying Glutes Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your legs extended. | Step:2 Bend your right knee and place your right ankle on your left thigh, just above the knee. | Step:3 Grasp your left thigh with both hands and gently pull it towards your chest. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds. | Step:5 Release and repeat on the other side.

name: Assisted Triceps Dip (Kneeling)
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the machine to your desired weight and height. | Step:2 Kneel down on the pad facing the machine, with your hands gripping the handles. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your elbows, keeping your back straight and close to the machine. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointing forward. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body, arms extended downwards. | Step:3 Bend at your hips and knees, lowering the dumbbells towards the ground while keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Push through your heels and extend your hips and knees, lifting the dumbbells back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Kneeling Bicep Curl Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Kneel on the floor with an exercise ball in front of you. | Step:2 Place your elbows on top of the exercise ball, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing up. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbells while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Bicep Curl With Stork Stance
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Extend one leg behind you, balancing on the toes of that foot. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the weights until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Full Maltese
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended straight out to the sides. | Step:2 Slowly lean forward, keeping your arms straight, until your upper body is parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Engage your core and hold this position for a few seconds. | Step:4 Return to the starting position by pushing through your feet and standing back up. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Seated Hammer Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with a neutral grip (palms facing each other). | Step:3 Rest your elbow on the inside of your thigh, just above the knee. | Step:4 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbell up towards your shoulder. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Cable Lying Extension Pullover (With Rope Attachment)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope to a cable machine and set the pulley at the highest position. | Step:2 Lie down on a bench with your head towards the cable machine. | Step:3 Hold the rope with both hands and extend your arms straight up above your chest. | Step:4 Keeping your arms straight, slowly lower the rope behind your head while maintaining control. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly raise the rope back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Roller Seated Shoulder Flexor Depresor Retractor
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a flat surface with your legs extended in front of you. | Step:2 Hold the roller with both hands, palms facing down, and place it on your thighs. | Step:3 Lean forward slightly and roll the roller away from your body, extending your arms straight in front of you. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly roll the roller back towards your body, bending your arms and bringing the roller back to your thighs. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Triceps Dip (Between Benches)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your hands gripping the edge of the bench, fingers pointing forward. | Step:2 Slide your butt off the bench, supporting your weight with your hands. | Step:3 Bend your elbows and lower your body towards the ground, keeping your back close to the bench. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Bicep Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your back against the pad. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and keep your elbows close to your sides. | Step:3 Exhale and curl the handles upward, contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the handles back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Standing Close Grip Military Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly closer than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lift the barbell to shoulder height, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:3 Press the barbell overhead, extending your arms fully. | Step:4 Lower the barbell back to shoulder height. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez Barbell Close Grip Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher curl bench and place your upper arms on the pad, gripping the ez barbell with an underhand grip. | Step:2 Rest your triceps on the pad and fully extend your arms, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Slowly curl the barbell towards your shoulders, contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Lower the barbell back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Wide-Grip Chest Dip On High Parallel Bars
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself on the parallel bars with your arms fully extended and your body suspended in the air. | Step:2 Lean forward slightly and lower your body by bending your elbows until your chest is just above the bars. | Step:3 Pause for a moment, then push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Elbow Dips
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a bench or chair with your hands gripping the edge next to your hips. | Step:2 Slide your hips forward off the bench and straighten your legs, keeping your heels on the ground. | Step:3 Bend your elbows and lower your body towards the ground, keeping your back close to the bench. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your hands to straighten your arms and lift your body back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Suspended Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing away from a suspension trainer with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend one leg forward and place the top of your foot in the foot cradle of the suspension trainer. | Step:3 Bend your standing leg and lower your body down into a lunge position, keeping your chest up and your knee in line with your toes. | Step:4 Push through your heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Single Leg Bridge With Outstretched Leg
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Extend one leg straight out in front of you. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and lift your hips off the ground, forming a straight line from your knees to your shoulders. | Step:4 Hold for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Seated Calf Stretch (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a chair or bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Extend one leg straight out in front of you, keeping your heel on the ground. | Step:3 Lean forward slightly, feeling a stretch in your calf muscle. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds. | Step:5 Switch legs and repeat the stretch.

name: Side-To-Side Toe Touch (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended to the sides. | Step:2 Bend at the waist to the right, reaching your right hand towards your right foot while keeping your left hand extended to the side. | Step:3 Return to the starting position and then bend at the waist to the left, reaching your left hand towards your left foot while keeping your right hand extended to the side. | Step:4 Repeat the side-to-side bending motion for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lateral To Front Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and engage your core. | Step:3 Raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the ground, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Next, raise your arms in front of you until they are parallel to the ground, again keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline One Arm Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench with a dumbbell in one hand, resting it on your thigh. | Step:2 Lean forward and position your upper arm against the inside of your thigh. | Step:3 Raise the dumbbell to the side, keeping your arm slightly bent and your palm facing down. | Step:4 Continue lifting until your arm is parallel to the floor. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Concentration Curl (On Stability Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with your palm facing up and your arm extended down towards the floor. | Step:3 Rest your elbow on the inside of your thigh, just above the knee. | Step:4 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbell up towards your shoulder while contracting your biceps. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms and repeat.

name: Dumbbell Alternating Seated Bicep Curl On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing forward and your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl one dumbbell while rotating your forearm until your palm is facing your shoulder. | Step:4 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the curl with the other arm. | Step:6 Continue alternating curls for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Overhead Triceps Extension (Rope Attachment)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope to a cable machine at a high position. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the rope with both hands, palms facing each other, and bring your hands above your head. | Step:4 Keep your upper arms close to your head and your elbows pointing forward. | Step:5 Slowly lower the rope behind your head by bending your elbows. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back up to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your palms facing away from you and your arms fully extended. | Step:2 Engage your core and squeeze your shoulder blades together. | Step:3 Pull your body up towards the bar by bending your elbows and bringing your chest towards the bar. | Step:4 Pause at the top of the movement, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Lying Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench with your chest against the pad and your arms extended over the edge, holding a barbell with an underhand grip. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the bar until your biceps are fully contracted and the bar is at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Seated Lower Back Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a chair with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands on your thighs or on the sides of the chair for support. | Step:3 Slowly lean forward from your hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Feel the stretch in your lower back and hold for 20-30 seconds. | Step:5 Slowly return to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Seated Leg Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the machine to fit your body and sit on it with your back against the backrest. | Step:2 Place your lower legs under the padded lever, just above your ankles. | Step:3 Grasp the handles on the sides of the machine for support. | Step:4 Keeping your upper legs stationary, exhale and curl your legs up as far as possible. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your hamstrings. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the lever back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Gripper Hands
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and grip the handles of the leverage machine. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Exhale and squeeze the handles, contracting your forearms. | Step:4 Hold the contraction for a second, then slowly release and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kneeling Push-Up (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Start by kneeling on the ground with your hands shoulder-width apart, fingers pointing forward. | Step:2 Extend your legs behind you, resting on the balls of your feet, so that your body forms a straight line from head to heels. | Step:3 Engage your core and lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your sides. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your chest is just above the ground, then push back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Standing Pelvic Tilt
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Place your hands on your hips or let them hang by your sides. | Step:3 Engage your core muscles and tilt your pelvis forward, pushing your lower back towards the wall behind you. | Step:4 Hold the position for a few seconds, then release and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Floor Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Place a barbell on the floor in front of you. | Step:2 Stand with the balls of your feet on the edge of the barbell, with your heels hanging off. | Step:3 Hold onto a stable object for balance if needed. | Step:4 Raise your heels as high as possible, using your calves to lift your body. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lying (Side) Quads Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your side with your legs straight. | Step:2 Bend your top leg and grab your ankle or foot with your hand. | Step:3 Gently pull your ankle or foot towards your glutes until you feel a stretch in your quads. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds. | Step:5 Release the stretch and repeat on the other side.

name: Triceps Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand or sit upright with your back straight. | Step:2 Extend one arm overhead, bending it at the elbow. | Step:3 Place your opposite hand on the bent elbow and gently pull it towards your head. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, feeling a gentle stretch in your triceps. | Step:5 Release the stretch and repeat on the other arm.

name: Squat To Overhead Reach With Twist
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:3 As you come up from the squat, raise your arms overhead and twist your torso to one side. | Step:4 Return to the starting position and repeat the squat, this time twisting your torso to the opposite side. | Step:5 Continue alternating sides with each squat repetition.

name: Kettlebell Plyo Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands on the kettlebells, shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your chest towards the ground, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:3 Push through your hands explosively, lifting your hands off the kettlebells and extending your arms fully. | Step:4 Land softly back on the kettlebells and immediately lower your chest back down for the next repetition. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Scapula Dips
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended in front of you. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your elbows and retracting your shoulder blades, as if you are trying to squeeze a pencil between them. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your hands to extend your elbows and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Front Shoulder Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and grasp the cable handle with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Raise the cable handle in front of you, keeping your arms straight and your palms facing down. | Step:4 Continue lifting until your arms are parallel to the floor. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the cable handle back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hack One Leg Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the sled machine to an appropriate weight. | Step:2 Stand on the sled machine with one foot, keeping the other foot off the ground. | Step:3 Hold onto the handles for stability. | Step:4 Raise your heel as high as possible, lifting your body up on the ball of your foot. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heel back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. | Step:7 Switch legs and repeat the exercise.

name: Dumbbell Incline Inner Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Rest your upper arms on the bench, allowing your elbows to hang down and your palms to face forward. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chair Leg Extended Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a chair with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Extend one leg straight out in front of you, keeping your heel on the ground. | Step:3 Lean forward slightly, feeling a stretch in your quadriceps. | Step:4 Hold this position for 20-30 seconds. | Step:5 Switch legs and repeat the stretch.

name: Single Arm Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands shoulder-width apart and one hand placed slightly wider than the other. | Step:2 Engage your core and lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 As you lower yourself, shift your weight to one side and lift the opposite arm off the ground, extending it straight out to the side. | Step:4 Push through your chest and triceps to raise your body back up to the starting position, while simultaneously lowering your extended arm back to the ground. | Step:5 Repeat the movement, alternating the arm you extend with each repetition.

name: Barbell Decline Wide-Grip Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a decline bench with your feet secured and your head lower than your hips. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with a wide grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lower the barbell to your chest, keeping your elbows out to the sides. | Step:4 Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying One Arm Deltoid Rear
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a flat bench with a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing inwards. | Step:2 Extend your arm straight down towards the floor, keeping it close to your body. | Step:3 Raise your arm up and back, squeezing your shoulder blade towards your spine. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arm back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Lever Reverse Grip Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the leverage machine. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an underhand grip, palms facing up. | Step:3 Rest your upper arms on the preacher pad, ensuring your elbows are fully extended. | Step:4 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the handles towards your shoulders. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the handles back to the starting position, fully extending your elbows. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Seesaw Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in each hand at shoulder height. | Step:2 Press one kettlebell overhead while keeping the other kettlebell at shoulder height. | Step:3 Lower the pressed kettlebell back to shoulder height while simultaneously pressing the other kettlebell overhead. | Step:4 Continue alternating the pressing motion, creating a seesaw-like movement. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell One Arm Floor Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with one hand, palm facing up, and extend your arm straight up over your chest. | Step:3 Slowly lower the barbell towards your chest, keeping your elbow close to your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Standing Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing forward and arm fully extended. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the weight upward while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the dumbbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbell is at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Roller Body Saw
instructions: Step:1 Start in a plank position with your forearms on the roller and your body in a straight line. | Step:2 Engage your core and slowly roll the roller forward, extending your body as far as you can while maintaining control. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the furthest point, then slowly roll the roller back towards your starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Jackknife Sit-Up
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your arms overhead. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs and upper body simultaneously, reaching your hands towards your toes. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs and upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Resistance Band Seated Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a chair or bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the resistance band with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and arms extended down by your sides. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the resistance band up towards your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the resistance band back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Standing Ab Rollerout
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the barbell with both hands in front of your thighs. | Step:2 Engage your core and slowly roll the barbell down towards the ground, keeping your back straight and your arms extended. | Step:3 Continue rolling the barbell forward until your body is fully extended and your hands are directly above your head. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly roll the barbell back towards your thighs, maintaining control and keeping your core engaged. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand, with your palms facing forward and your arms extended above your chest. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbells slowly to the sides of your chest, keeping your elbows at a 90-degree angle. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then push the dumbbells back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Incline Close-Grip Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Place your hands on an elevated surface, such as a bench or step, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend your legs behind you, resting on the balls of your feet, with your body forming a straight line from head to heels. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the elevated surface by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your sides. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Decline Shrug
instructions: Step:1 Set up a decline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Lie face down on the bench with your chest and stomach resting against it. | Step:3 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended towards the floor. | Step:4 Keeping your arms straight, raise your shoulders towards your ears as high as possible. | Step:5 Hold the contraction for a moment, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Lunge
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and a barbell resting on your upper back. | Step:2 Take a step forward with your right foot, keeping your torso upright. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your right knee until your thigh is parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with your left leg, alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Standing Bradford Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the barbell in front of your shoulders with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Press the barbell overhead, fully extending your arms. | Step:3 Lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Thruster
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell at shoulder height with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Lower into a squat position by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:3 As you reach the bottom of the squat, explosively drive through your heels to stand up, simultaneously pressing the barbell overhead. | Step:4 Lower the barbell back to shoulder height as you lower back into the squat position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Supported Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at your sides. | Step:2 Keeping your chest up and core engaged, slowly lower your body down by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:3 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Overhead Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with a wide grip, positioning it overhead with your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Engage your core and lower your body down into a squat position, keeping your chest up and knees tracking over your toes. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Reverse Grip Decline Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a decline bench with your feet secured and your head lower than your hips. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with a reverse grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Assisted Inverse Leg Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine so that the ankle attachment is at the lowest setting. | Step:2 Lie face down on the bench with your legs straight and the ankle attachment secured to your ankles. | Step:3 Hold onto the handles of the bench for stability. | Step:4 Keeping your upper body stationary, exhale and curl your legs up towards your glutes by flexing your knees. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your hamstrings. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower your legs back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest Stretch With Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold the exercise ball with both hands and extend your arms straight out in front of you. | Step:3 Slowly bring the exercise ball towards your chest, feeling a stretch in your chest muscles. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for a few seconds, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Split Squat V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper back. | Step:2 Take a large step forward with your right foot, keeping your torso upright. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your knees and hips until your right thigh is parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then push through your right heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with your left leg forward for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Standing Wheel Rollerout
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing tall with your feet shoulder-width apart and the wheel roller in front of you. | Step:2 Bend at your waist and slowly roll the wheel forward, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Continue rolling forward until you feel a stretch in your abs and your body is extended as far as possible. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly roll the wheel back towards your body, returning to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Plyo Push Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your chest towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping your body in a straight line. | Step:3 Push explosively off the ground, using your chest muscles to propel your upper body off the ground. | Step:4 Land softly with your hands back in the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward and arms fully extended. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Low Bar Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and the barbell resting on your upper back. | Step:2 Keeping your chest up and core engaged, slowly lower your body by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:3 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground or slightly below. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, with the band placed just above your knees. | Step:2 Keeping your chest up and core engaged, push your hips back and bend your knees to lower into a squat position. | Step:3 Make sure your knees are tracking over your toes and your weight is in your heels. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Reverse Spider Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body and arms fully extended. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Chest Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your back flat against the pad. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and position your elbows at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Push the handles forward until your arms are fully extended, exhaling during the movement. | Step:4 Pause briefly at the end of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position, inhaling as you do so. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest Dip
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself on parallel bars with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:2 Lower your body by bending your elbows until your shoulders are below your elbows. | Step:3 Push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Hammer Grip Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the leverage machine. | Step:2 Place your upper arms on the preacher pad, ensuring your chest is pressed against it. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with a hammer grip (palms facing each other). | Step:4 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the handles towards your shoulders. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the handles back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Alternate Overhead Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder level with your palms facing forward. | Step:2 Press one dumbbell overhead, fully extending your arm. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbell back to shoulder level. | Step:4 Repeat with the other arm. | Step:5 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Overhead Triceps Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand or sit upright with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend one arm overhead, bending at the elbow so that your hand reaches towards the opposite shoulder blade. | Step:3 With your other hand, gently pull the elbow of the extended arm towards the opposite side of your head, feeling a stretch in your triceps. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, then release. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side.

name: Weighted Svend Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a weight plate in front of your chest with both hands. | Step:2 Keep your elbows slightly bent and your palms facing each other. | Step:3 Press the weight plate straight out in front of you, fully extending your arms. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, then slowly bring the weight plate back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Close-Grip Push-Up (On Knees)
instructions: Step:1 Start by getting on your hands and knees, with your hands shoulder-width apart and your knees hip-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your upper body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your sides. | Step:3 Pause for a moment when your chest is just above the ground. | Step:4 Push through your palms to straighten your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell One Leg Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell across your upper back. | Step:2 Lift one foot off the ground and extend it forward, keeping it parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Bend your standing leg and lower your body down as if sitting back into a chair, keeping your chest up and your back straight. | Step:4 Lower yourself until your thigh is parallel to the ground, then push through your heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Lean Planche
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands shoulder-width apart and your body straight. | Step:2 Engage your core and slowly shift your weight forward, bringing your shoulders past your hands. | Step:3 Keep your elbows slightly bent and your body straight as you lean forward. | Step:4 Hold this position for a few seconds, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Iron Cross
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at your sides. | Step:2 Raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the ground, forming a T shape with your body. | Step:3 Pause for a moment, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the leverage machine. | Step:2 Place your upper arms on the pad and grip the handles with an underhand grip. | Step:3 Keep your back straight and your elbows positioned on the pad. | Step:4 Exhale and curl your forearms towards your upper arms, contracting your biceps. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the handles back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push-Up On Lower Arms
instructions: Step:1 Start in a plank position with your forearms on the ground and elbows directly below your shoulders. | Step:2 Engage your core and keep your body in a straight line from head to toe. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Straddle Maltese
instructions: Step:1 Start by hanging from a pair of rings with your arms fully extended and your body in a straight line. | Step:2 Spread your legs wide apart, forming a straddle position. | Step:3 Engage your core and slowly lower your body until your arms are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Hold this position for a few seconds, then push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl Reverse
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing down and arms fully extended. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Stiff Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, hinge at the hips and lower the dumbbells towards the ground, allowing a slight bend in your knees. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbells until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings, then squeeze your glutes and push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline One Arm Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench with a dumbbell in one hand, resting on your thigh. | Step:2 Lie back on the bench and position the dumbbell at shoulder level, palm facing forward. | Step:3 Press the dumbbell upward and slightly inward, extending your arm fully. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Barbell Biceps Curl (With Arm Blaster)
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with an underhand grip, palms facing up. | Step:2 Place your upper arms against the arm blaster, keeping your elbows close to your torso. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the barbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the bar is at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Reverse Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench with your chest against the pad and your arms extended straight down, holding a barbell with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the barbell upward while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the barbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the barbell is at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push-Up (On Stability Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Place the stability ball on the ground and position yourself facing down with your hands on the ball, shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend your legs straight out behind you, balancing on your toes. | Step:3 Engage your core and lower your chest towards the ball by bending your elbows, keeping your body in a straight line. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Korean Dips
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself between two parallel bars with your arms extended and supporting your body weight. | Step:2 Lower your body by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Pause for a moment, then push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Seated Hip Adduction
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your back against the backrest. | Step:2 Place your feet on the footrests and grasp the handles for stability. | Step:3 Engage your adductor muscles and slowly bring your legs together, squeezing your inner thighs. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the peak contraction, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Pullover
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your head at one end and your feet on the floor. | Step:2 Hold a barbell with a shoulder-width grip and extend your arms straight above your chest. | Step:3 Keeping your arms straight, lower the barbell behind your head in a controlled manner until you feel a stretch in your lats. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then raise the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl V Sit On Bosu Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bosu ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing forward and your arms fully extended down by your sides. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Pullover
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your head at one end and your feet on the floor. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell with both hands and extend your arms straight above your chest. | Step:3 Keeping a slight bend in your elbows, slowly lower the dumbbell behind your head until you feel a stretch in your chest and shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then raise the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cocoons
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your torso is at a 45-degree angle. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Side Hip (On Parallel Bars)
instructions: Step:1 Stand between two parallel bars with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Place your hands on the bars and lift your body off the ground, supporting your weight on your arms. | Step:3 Engage your abs and slowly lift your legs to the side, keeping them straight. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Supine Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your back and head supported, and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing up and your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the weights until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Alternate Heel Touchers
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight out to the sides, parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, lift your shoulders off the ground and reach your right hand towards your right heel. | Step:4 Return to the starting position and repeat on the left side, reaching your left hand towards your left heel. | Step:5 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Supination On Floor
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back on the floor with your legs extended and your arms by your sides, holding a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Rotate your palms to face up, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:3 Slowly curl the dumbbells towards your shoulders, squeezing your forearms. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Pull Through (With Rope)
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing away from the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Grab the rope attachment with both hands and step forward, creating tension in the cable. | Step:3 Bend at the hips and lower your upper body until it is parallel to the ground, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Engage your glutes and hamstrings to pull your body back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sled Calf Press On Leg Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat of the leg press machine so that your knees are slightly bent when your feet are on the sled. | Step:2 Place your feet shoulder-width apart on the sled, with your toes pointing forward. | Step:3 Release the safety handles and push the sled away from you by extending your knees and ankles. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the sled back down by bending your knees and ankles. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez Barbell Reverse Grip Curl
