instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the ez barbell with an underhand grip. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. | Step:3 Curl the barbell upwards by contracting your biceps, while exhaling. | Step:4 Continue to raise the barbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the barbell is at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Slowly begin to bring the barbell back to the starting position as you inhale. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Decline Sit-Up
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a decline bench with your feet secured under the foot pads. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head or across your chest. | Step:3 Engage your abs and slowly lift your upper body off the bench, curling forward until your torso is perpendicular to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Rear Lunge
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Take a step backward with your right foot, lowering your body into a lunge position. | Step:3 Bend your left knee and lower your body until your left thigh is parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then push through your left heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side, stepping back with your left foot.

name: Dumbbell Seated One Leg Calf Raise - Hammer Grip
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your feet flat on the ground and a dumbbell resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Place one foot on a raised surface, such as a step or block, with your heel hanging off the edge. | Step:3 Hold the dumbbell with a hammer grip, meaning your palms are facing each other and your fingers are wrapped around the handle. | Step:4 Keeping your core engaged and your back straight, slowly raise your heel as high as possible by pushing through the ball of your foot. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heel back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other leg.

name: Assisted Seated Pectoralis Major Stretch With Stability Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a stability ball with both hands and extend your arms straight out in front of you. | Step:3 Slowly lower the stability ball towards your chest, feeling a stretch in your pectoral muscles. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for a few seconds, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Concentration Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your legs spread apart and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold one end of the band in your hand and step on the other end with your foot on the same side. | Step:3 Lean forward slightly and rest your elbow on the inside of your thigh, just above the knee. | Step:4 With your palm facing up, slowly curl your hand towards your shoulder, keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your hand back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Push-Up (Bosu Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Place the bosu ball on the ground with the flat side facing up. | Step:2 Position yourself in a push-up position with your hands on the outer edges of the bosu ball. | Step:3 Engage your core and lower your body down towards the bosu ball by bending your elbows. | Step:4 Push yourself back up to the starting position by extending your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Alternate Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward and arms fully extended. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, alternating arms.

name: Barbell Standing Reverse Grip Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with an underhand grip, palms facing up. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and your upper arms stationary. | Step:3 Exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps, bringing the barbell as close to your shoulders as possible. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Spider Crawl Push Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your feet together. | Step:2 Bring your right knee towards your right elbow, keeping it off the ground. | Step:3 As you bring your right knee back, simultaneously lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows. | Step:4 Push back up to the starting position and repeat with your left knee towards your left elbow. | Step:5 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Swing 360
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold your arms straight out in front of you, parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Engage your core and swing your arms in a circular motion, rotating your torso as you do so. | Step:4 Continue the circular motion, swinging your arms and rotating your torso for the desired number of repetitions. | Step:5 Remember to breathe throughout the exercise.

name: Chin-Up
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your palms facing towards you and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and pull your body up towards the bar, leading with your chest. | Step:3 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Alternate Front Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body and arms extended down by your sides. | Step:3 Keeping your arms straight, raise one dumbbell in front of you until it is parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with the other arm. | Step:6 Alternate between arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Alternating Press On Floor
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying on your back on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a kettlebell in each hand, with your palms facing towards your feet and your arms extended straight up towards the ceiling. | Step:3 Lower one kettlebell down towards your shoulder while keeping the other kettlebell extended straight up. | Step:4 Press the lowered kettlebell back up to the starting position while simultaneously lowering the other kettlebell down towards your shoulder. | Step:5 Continue alternating the press motion with each kettlebell for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Kneeling Leg Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the machine to fit your body and select the desired weight. | Step:2 Kneel on the machine facing downwards, with your knees resting on the pad and your feet secured under the footpads. | Step:3 Grasp the handles or the sides of the machine for stability. | Step:4 Keeping your upper body stationary, exhale and curl your legs up towards your glutes by flexing your knees. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your hamstrings. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower your legs back to the starting position, fully extending your knees. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Twisted Leg Raise (Female)
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Bend your knees and lift your legs off the ground, bringing them towards your chest. | Step:3 As you lift your legs, twist your hips to one side, bringing your knees towards your opposite shoulder. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the movement, this time twisting your hips to the other side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand with your palm facing your body. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:3 Raise the dumbbell to the side, keeping your arm straight and your palm facing down. | Step:4 Continue lifting until your arm is parallel to the ground. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell Cuban Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height with your palms facing down. | Step:2 Keeping your core engaged and your elbows slightly bent, press the dumbbells up and overhead until your arms are fully extended. | Step:3 Rotate your wrists so that your palms are facing forward. | Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position, rotating your wrists back to the starting position as you do so. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Standing Wide Grip Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with an underhand grip, hands wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your elbows close to your torso. | Step:3 Exhale and curl the barbell up towards your shoulders, keeping your upper arms stationary. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Press On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Hold the cable handles at chest height with your palms facing down and your elbows bent. | Step:3 Engage your core and press the cable handles forward until your arms are fully extended. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly release the tension and bring the cable handles back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Seated Good Morning
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and a barbell resting on your upper back. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your chest up. | Step:3 Slowly hinge forward at the hips, lowering your torso towards the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Curl
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and sit on it with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Rest your upper arms on the incline bench and let your elbows hang down, fully extending your arms. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Assisted Prone Hamstring
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a mat or bench with your legs fully extended. | Step:2 Have a partner or use a resistance band to secure your ankles. | Step:3 Engage your hamstrings and lift your legs towards your glutes, keeping your knees straight. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable High Pulley Overhead Tricep Extension
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope to a high pulley and stand facing away from the machine. | Step:2 Grasp the rope with both hands and extend your arms overhead. | Step:3 Keep your elbows close to your head and your upper arms stationary. | Step:4 Slowly lower the rope behind your head by bending your elbows. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Standing Inner Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Grasp the cable handle with an underhand grip, palms facing up. | Step:3 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary. | Step:4 Exhale and curl the cable handle towards your shoulders, contracting your biceps. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the cable handle back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Extended Range One Arm Press On Floor
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying on your back on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a kettlebell in one hand, with your palm facing towards your feet. | Step:3 Extend your arm straight up towards the ceiling, keeping your elbow locked and your wrist straight. | Step:4 Slowly lower the kettlebell back down to the starting position, maintaining control throughout the movement. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Kettlebell One Arm Military Press To The Side
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in one hand at shoulder height. | Step:2 Engage your core and keep your back straight. | Step:3 Press the kettlebell overhead, extending your arm fully. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the kettlebell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Glute Bridge Two Legs On Bench (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a bench with your back against it and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands on the bench beside your hips for support. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and hamstrings, then lift your hips off the bench until your body forms a straight line from your knees to your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Decline Fly
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a decline bench with your feet secured and your head lower than your hips. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing each other and your arms extended above your chest. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbells out to the sides in a wide arc until you feel a stretch in your chest. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then squeeze your chest muscles to bring the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Lunge With Swing
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a weight in each hand. | Step:2 Take a step forward with your right foot, lowering your body into a lunge position. | Step:3 As you lunge forward, swing the weights forward and upward, keeping your arms straight. | Step:4 Push off with your right foot and return to the starting position, swinging the weights back down. | Step:5 Repeat with your left foot and continue alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Incline Push-Up (On Box)
instructions: Step:1 Place your hands on the edge of a box or elevated surface, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend your legs behind you, resting on the balls of your feet, creating a straight line from your head to your heels. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the box by bending your elbows, keeping your body in a straight line. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Elbow Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other and arms extended straight up over your chest. | Step:2 Lower the dumbbells towards your shoulders by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then press the dumbbells back up to the starting position by extending your elbows. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Hammer Press
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and sit on it with a dumbbell in each hand, resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Lie back on the bench and position the dumbbells at shoulder level with your palms facing each other. | Step:3 Press the dumbbells up and away from your body until your arms are fully extended. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Shoulder Raise
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and sit on it with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing down. | Step:2 Rest the dumbbells on your thighs and lean back onto the bench. | Step:3 Use your thighs to help raise the dumbbells to shoulder height, then rotate your wrists so that your palms are facing forward. | Step:4 Exhale and slowly raise the dumbbells above your head, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Three Bench Dips
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a bench with your hands gripping the edge, fingers pointing forward. | Step:2 Walk your feet forward, sliding your butt off the bench and supporting your weight with your arms. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your elbows, keeping your back close to the bench. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing One Arm Concentration Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing up. | Step:2 Place your free hand on your thigh for support. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder by contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbell is at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Band Single Leg Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and place a resistance band around your ankles. | Step:2 Take a big step forward with your right foot and a smaller step back with your left foot. | Step:3 Bend your knees and lower your body until your right thigh is parallel to the ground, keeping your left knee slightly above the ground. | Step:4 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side.

name: Exercise Ball On The Wall Calf Raise (Tennis Ball Between Knees)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your back against a wall and place an exercise ball between your lower back and the wall. | Step:2 Position your feet shoulder-width apart and slightly in front of you. | Step:3 Hold a dumbbell in each hand, with your arms extended by your sides. | Step:4 Place a tennis ball between your knees. | Step:5 Raise your heels off the ground, lifting your body up onto your toes. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Neutral Grip Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with a neutral grip (palms facing each other) and your arms extended straight up over your chest. | Step:3 Slowly lower the dumbbells down towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the dumbbells back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Lying Close-Grip Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your head at the end of the bench. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with a close grip, hands shoulder-width apart, palms facing up. | Step:3 Extend your arms fully, lifting the barbell above your chest. | Step:4 Keeping your upper arms stationary, slowly lower the barbell towards your forehead by bending your elbows. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Rear Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on the bench with your chest against the backrest and hold a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight down with your palms facing each other. | Step:4 Keeping a slight bend in your elbows, raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez Barbell Decline Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a decline bench with your head lower than your feet and your feet secured. | Step:2 Hold the ez barbell with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Extend your arms fully, keeping your elbows close to your head. | Step:4 Lower the barbell slowly towards your forehead, bending your elbows. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez Barbell Reverse Grip Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher bench with your chest against the pad and your feet flat on the floor. | Step:2 Grasp the ez barbell with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Rest your upper arms on the pad, allowing your forearms to hang down. | Step:4 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the barbell up towards your shoulders. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Otis Up
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your torso is at a 45-degree angle. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated One Arm Kickback
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in one hand. | Step:2 Bend your torso forward at the waist, keeping your back straight and parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Extend your arm straight back, keeping your elbow close to your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Frog Planche
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands shoulder-width apart and your feet together. | Step:2 Bend your elbows and lower your body towards the ground, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 As you lower your body, lift your feet off the ground and bring your knees towards your chest. | Step:4 Hold this position for a few seconds, then extend your legs back out and push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Close-Grip Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Place a band around your upper arms, just above the elbows. | Step:2 Assume a push-up position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body in a straight line from head to heels. | Step:3 Bend your elbows and lower your chest towards the ground, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:4 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Seated Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a kettlebell in each hand at shoulder height, palms facing forward. | Step:3 Press the kettlebells overhead, fully extending your arms. | Step:4 Lower the kettlebells back to shoulder height. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Femoral
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and a dumbbell resting on your lower abdomen. | Step:2 Bend your knees and bring the dumbbell towards your glutes, keeping your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Triceps Dip On High Parallel Bars
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself between two parallel bars with your hands gripping the bars and your arms fully extended. | Step:2 Bend your elbows and lower your body until your upper arms are parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Pause for a moment, then push through your palms to straighten your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Single Leg Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Take a step forward with one foot and position your feet so that your front foot is flat on the ground and your back foot is elevated on a bench or step. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your front knee and hip, keeping your back knee slightly bent and your back heel off the ground. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your front thigh is parallel to the ground, then push through your front heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Quick Feet V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Begin by rapidly moving your feet up and down, as if you were running in place. | Step:3 Keep your movements quick and light, focusing on staying on the balls of your feet. | Step:4 Continue for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lunge With Bicep Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing forward. | Step:2 Take a step forward with your right foot, lowering your body into a lunge position. Your right knee should be bent at a 90-degree angle and your left knee should be hovering just above the ground. | Step:3 As you lunge forward, simultaneously curl the dumbbells towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the lunge, then push through your right heel to return to the starting position, lowering the dumbbells back down to your sides. | Step:5 Repeat the lunge and bicep curl on the opposite side, stepping forward with your left foot. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez Barbell Spider Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the ez barbell with an underhand grip, palms facing up. | Step:2 Rest your upper arms on a preacher bench or stability ball, allowing your elbows to hang down. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the barbell up towards your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Cross Body Hammer Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body. | Step:2 Keep your elbows close to your torso and your upper arms stationary. | Step:3 Exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps, bringing the dumbbells across your body towards your opposite shoulder. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Concentration Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your legs spread apart and a dumbbell in one hand, resting your elbow on the inside of your thigh. | Step:2 Fully extend your arm and hold the dumbbell with an underhand grip. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the weight up towards your shoulder while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbell is at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Frankenstein Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the barbell in front of your body with straight arms. | Step:2 Keeping your back straight, lower your body by bending at the knees and hips, as if sitting back into a chair. | Step:3 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a low pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Rest your forearms on a bench or pad, with your wrists hanging off the edge. | Step:5 Keeping your forearms stationary, exhale and curl your wrists upward as far as possible. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the bar back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Medicine Ball Chest Push From 3 Point Stance
instructions: Step:1 Start in a 3 point stance with one hand on the medicine ball and the other hand on the ground. | Step:2 Extend your legs and position your body in a straight line. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the ground while keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Push the medicine ball away from your body, extending your arm fully. | Step:5 Return to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hack Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the sled machine to a comfortable weight. | Step:2 Stand on the sled machine with your toes on the platform and your heels hanging off. | Step:3 Hold onto the handles for stability. | Step:4 Raise your heels as high as possible by pushing through the balls of your feet. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Flutter Kicks
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your hands by your sides. | Step:2 Engage your core and lift your legs off the ground about 6 inches. | Step:3 Keeping your legs straight, alternate lifting one leg slightly higher than the other. | Step:4 Continue this fluttering motion for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Decline Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Place your hands on the ground slightly wider than shoulder-width apart, with your feet elevated on a stable surface. | Step:2 Keep your body in a straight line from head to toe, engaging your core muscles. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body. | Step:4 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Wide Grip Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your palms facing away from you and your hands wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and squeeze your shoulder blades together. | Step:3 Pull your body up towards the bar until your chin is above the bar. | Step:4 Lower your body back down to the starting position with control. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Decline Hammer Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a decline bench with your feet secured and your head lower than your hips. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing each other and your arms extended above your chest. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbells to the sides of your chest, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:4 Press the dumbbells back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Side Lying Hip Adduction (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your side with your legs straight and stacked on top of each other. | Step:2 Place your bottom arm under your head for support. | Step:3 Engage your adductors and lift your top leg as high as possible without rotating your hips or leaning backward. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your leg back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Band V-Up
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs straight and your arms extended overhead, holding the band. | Step:2 Engaging your abs, lift your legs and upper body off the ground simultaneously, reaching your hands towards your toes. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs and upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hamstring Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Step forward with your right foot and shift your weight onto your right leg. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight, slowly bend forward at the hips, reaching towards your right foot with both hands. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, then return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side.

name: Three Bench Dip
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your hands gripping the edge, fingers pointing forward. | Step:2 Slide your butt off the bench, supporting your weight with your hands. | Step:3 Bend your elbows and lower your body until your upper arms are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Bench Front Squat
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and the barbell resting on your upper chest, just below your collarbone. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip, keeping your elbows up and your upper arms parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Lower your body down into a squat position by bending at the knees and hips, keeping your back straight and your chest up. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the squat, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Decline Bent Arm Pullover
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on a decline bench with your head lower than your hips and your feet secured. | Step:2 Hold a barbell with a pronated grip (palms facing away from you) and extend your arms straight above your chest. | Step:3 Lower the barbell behind your head in a controlled manner, keeping your arms slightly bent. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then raise the barbell back to the starting position by contracting your lats. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Alternating V-Up
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs straight and your arms extended overhead, holding the band. | Step:2 Engage your abs and lift your legs and upper body off the ground simultaneously, reaching your hands towards your toes. | Step:3 As you lower your legs and upper body back down, switch the position of your legs, crossing one over the other. | Step:4 Repeat the movement, alternating the position of your legs with each repetition. | Step:5 Continue for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Resistance Band Seated Chest Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a chair or bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the resistance band handles in each hand, with your palms facing down and elbows bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Extend your arms forward, pushing the resistance band away from your chest. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sit-Up With Arms On Chest
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Cross your arms over your chest. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, lift your upper body off the ground towards your knees. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Seated Bicep Curl (On Stability Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a medicine ball with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and let your arms hang down by your sides. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the medicine ball up towards your shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the medicine ball back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ring Dips
instructions: Step:1 Start by hanging from the rings with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:2 Lower your body by bending your elbows until your shoulders are below your elbows. | Step:3 Push yourself back up to the starting position by straightening your arms. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise Ball Back Extension With Hands Behind Head
instructions: Step:1 Place the stability ball on the ground and lie face down on top of it with your hips resting on the ball. | Step:2 Position your feet against a wall or other stable surface for support. | Step:3 Cross your arms behind your head, with your hands touching the back of your head. | Step:4 Engage your core and slowly lift your upper body off the ball, extending your back until your body forms a straight line from your head to your hips. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Revers Wrist Curl V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent. | Step:2 Hold a barbell with an overhand grip, palms facing down, and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Rest your forearms on your thighs, allowing your wrists to hang off the edge. | Step:4 Keeping your forearms stationary, exhale and curl your wrists upward as far as possible. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause, then inhale and slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Tate Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a flat bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Raise the dumbbells to shoulder height, then rotate your wrists so that your palms are facing away from you. | Step:3 Press the dumbbells up until your arms are fully extended, then lower them back down to shoulder height. | Step:4 Rotate your wrists back to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Seated Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height so that your knees are slightly bent and your feet are flat on the footplate. | Step:2 Place your toes on the footplate with your heels hanging off the edge. | Step:3 Grasp the handles or the sides of the seat for stability. | Step:4 Push through the balls of your feet to raise your heels as high as possible. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Neck Side Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand or sit up straight with your shoulders relaxed. | Step:2 Tilt your head to one side, bringing your ear towards your shoulder. | Step:3 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds. | Step:4 Repeat on the other side. | Step:5 Perform 2-4 sets on each side.

name: Dumbbell Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a preacher curl bench with your upper arms resting on the pad and your chest against it. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing up and your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Alternate Shoulder
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing inwards, and raise them to shoulder height. | Step:3 Press one dumbbell up overhead while keeping the other dumbbell at shoulder height. | Step:4 Lower the raised dumbbell back to shoulder height while simultaneously pressing the other dumbbell up overhead. | Step:5 Continue alternating between arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sit-Up V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head with your elbows pointing outwards. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your torso is at a 45-degree angle. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Side Wrist Pull Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended in front of you. | Step:2 Extend your right arm out to the side, parallel to the ground, with your palm facing down. | Step:3 With your left hand, grab your right hand and gently pull it towards your body, feeling a stretch in your right forearm. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, then release. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side.

name: Kick Out Sit
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a bench or chair with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Lean back slightly and place your hands on the edge of the bench or chair for support. | Step:3 Engaging your hamstrings, lift your feet off the ground and extend your legs straight out in front of you. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly bend your knees and bring your feet back towards your body. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bench Dip (Knees Bent)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a bench or chair with your hands gripping the edge next to your hips. | Step:2 Slide your butt off the bench and straighten your legs in front of you, keeping your heels on the ground. | Step:3 Bend your elbows and lower your body towards the ground, keeping your back close to the bench. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push yourself back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Leg Pull In Flat Bench
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a flat bench with your legs extended straight out in front of you. | Step:2 Place your hands on the bench beside your hips for support. | Step:3 Engage your abs and lift your legs off the ground, bringing your knees towards your chest. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Glute-Ham Raise
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the glute-ham raise machine to fit your body. | Step:2 Position yourself face down on the machine with your ankles secured. | Step:3 Place your hands on your chest or cross them over your chest. | Step:4 Engage your hamstrings and glutes to lift your upper body up towards the ceiling. | Step:5 Continue lifting until your body is in a straight line from your head to your heels. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying Supination
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing up and your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, curl the dumbbells towards your shoulders by contracting your forearms. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Rope Incline Tricep Extension
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope to a high pulley and adjust the incline bench to a comfortable angle. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the pulley with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the rope with an overhand grip and extend your arms straight overhead. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your head and your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Lower the rope behind your head by bending your elbows until your forearms touch your biceps. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Standing Concentration Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell in one hand, palm facing up. | Step:2 Rest your opposite hand on your thigh for support. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, exhale and curl the weight up towards your shoulder. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, squeezing your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly lower the weight back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Cable Reverse Preacher Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine so that the preacher curl pad is at chest height. | Step:2 Sit on the preacher curl bench and place your upper arms on the pad, with your palms facing down and your elbows fully extended. | Step:3 Grab the cable handles with an underhand grip, shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the handles towards your shoulders, contracting your biceps. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower the handles back to the starting position, fully extending your elbows. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Seated Bradford Rocky Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lift the barbell to shoulder height, keeping your elbows slightly bent and pointing forward. | Step:4 Press the barbell overhead, fully extending your arms. | Step:5 Lower the barbell back to shoulder height and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Machine Incline Tricep Extension
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat of the smith machine so that the bar is at shoulder height. | Step:2 Sit on the bench with your back against the pad and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Extend your arms fully, lifting the bar off the rack and holding it directly above your chest. | Step:5 Lower the bar slowly towards your forehead, keeping your elbows close to your head. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the bar back up to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Olympic Barbell Hammer Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold an Olympic barbell with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Let the barbell hang at arm's length in front of your thighs, with your palms facing your body. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the barbell until your biceps are fully contracted and the barbell is at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: V-Sit On Floor
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your legs extended in front of you. | Step:2 Lean back slightly and lift your legs off the ground, keeping them straight. | Step:3 Simultaneously, lift your upper body off the ground and reach your arms towards your legs. | Step:4 Hold this position for a few seconds, then slowly lower your upper body and legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push Up On Bosu Ball
instructions: Step:1 Place the bosu ball on the ground with the flat side facing up. | Step:2 Position yourself in a push-up position with your hands on the outer edges of the bosu ball. | Step:3 Engage your core and lower your body down towards the bosu ball by bending your elbows. | Step:4 Push yourself back up to the starting position by extending your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Side Hip Abduction
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands on your hips. | Step:2 Shift your weight to one leg and lift the opposite leg out to the side, keeping it straight. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your leg back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat on the other side. | Step:5 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Hammer Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your torso and arms extended straight down. | Step:2 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:3 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:5 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.
